column5: Des

1= Manual Reset sequencing; 0 = Hardware Reset Sequencing (default). Pin reset RESETN leaves the gearbox device in a fully reset state.  Bringing the device into an operational state requires sequencing of SERDES reset signals.  Two sequencing methods are supported: Manual, and hardware sequenced.  This bit selects which method controls internal reset signals.  When Manual control is selected fields in register 30.44 control internal reset signals, otherwise bits in this register control them.
Select OTU framing protocol for protocol lock State Machine.

column4: 0=normal operation; 1=disable Tx if source indicates LOL
0=normal operation; 1=disable Tx if source indicates LOL

column5: This bit controls Ingress datapath reset signals, if hardware reset sequencing is selected (30.0.15=0). Asserting this bit resets the Ingress datapath of the gearbox.  De-asserting this bit causes a sequenced removal of reset from the Ingress datapath using the hardware reset sequencer. This bit is set to a one by assertion of the RESETN pin.

1=Ingress Datapath Reset Sequencer Inactive.  This bit is de-asserted whilst the Ingress hardware reset sequencer is in operation.  This bit is asserted when the hardware reset sequencer finishes operations, or is inactive.

This bit controls Egress datapath reset signals, if hardware reset sequencing is selected (30.0.15=0). Asserting this bit resets the Egress datapath of the gearbox.  De-asserting this bit causes a sequenced removal of reset from the Egress datapath using the hardware reset sequencer.  This bit is set to a one by assertion of the RESETN pin.

1=Egress Datapath Reset Sequencer Inactive.  This bit is de-asserted whilst the Egress hardware reset sequencer is in operation.  This bit is asserted when the hardware reset sequencer finishes operations, or is inactive.

Writing a one to this bit locations sets all MDIO registers except registers 30.0 (this register) ,register 30.62 (lane power downs), registers 30.180-182 (refclk select and PLL trim), and register 8.7 (PMA type)  to their default states. This bit must be written to a zero again to release the reset.

column4: 000 = PRBS31; 001 = PRBS9; 010 = reserved; 011 = reserved; 100 = PRBS31; 101 = PRBS23; 110 = PRBS15; 111 = PRBS7
column5: Receiver pattern verifier type : if prbs_autovr=0 this field selects pattern type; if  prbs_autovr=1 this field displays the pattern type locked to;
Disable  lane SERDES transmitter: 1= Disabled; 0 = Enabled; Note default value of this bit is 0 - Disabled

Writing a one to this bit causes the contents of the custom pattern generation register to be XOR'ed with the transmit data for the lane for one cycle only. This bit must be cleared and set again in order to insert another error. Error insertion is not gated by pattern generator enable.
